Job offer

Delegate Producer - MUNDIAL Montreal

DESCRIPTION OF THE COMPANY

Founded in 1994, Avalanche Prod is a Montreal-based company specializing in event architecture and turnkey production of several events, festivals and markets for the cultural and entertainment sectors, particularly in music and digital creativity.

Mundial Montreal is an annual showcase and networking event that introduces the best Canadian and international world music artists to key players in the national and international music scene, generating business development and relationship building opportunities. After ten editions, Mundial Montreal is firmly established as the key world music showcase and conference festival in North America.

ROLE

Under the authority of the general management and in collaboration with the members of the Avalanche Prod team, the Delegate Producer is responsible for the implementation of projects and the development of Mundial. As such, they are responsible for setting up an operational, material and financial plan dedicated to the proper functioning and growth of the event under their responsibility and for managing the team to support the required actions. They are responsible for the optimal use of resources and the implementation of business practices that allow the smooth running of all activities related to MUNDIAL.

MAIN RESPONSIBILITIES

Based on the strategic orientations, objectives and missions of MUNDIAL Montreal, the successful candidate will be responsible for the following functions

Administration (20%)

Develop budgets and follow up on budgetary matters;

Supervise and ensure the smooth running of the events and the achievement of the development objectives set by the management committee;

Design and manage the planning and coordination tools for the various production and communication teams;

Draft, negotiate, and ensure the follow-up of agreements with the various suppliers and service partners (technical equipment, caterers, etc.);

Supervise production of editorial content and post-event reports for various grant applications;

Production / Programming (50%)

Manage and facilitate production meetings (prepare agendas, conduct follow-ups, etc.);

Participate in management committee meetings, follow up and report to the teams

Oversee the proper management of the technical needs of the showcasing artists and the activities scheduled in the various venues of the events;

Oversee the management of the various sites of the event (follow-up of reservations, co-production and production agreements, cost reports) for showcases, public shows, panels, conferences and networking activities;

Manage ticketing and revenue distribution with promoters for all venues and activities. Produce tools for tracking and accounting of admissions and revenue;

Oversee the management of the reception team during events (venue managers, volunteers, messengers);

Ensure the confirmation of headlining artists within the deadlines set for the sale of indoor shows;

Oversee the calls for applications (online forms, distribution, identification of technical needs for the selected artists, sending rejection letters, managing deadlines and deliverables, managing contracts for selected artists);

Participate in the recruitment and coordinate the invitations made to international delegates from 20 different countries (send invitations, establish a grid of benefits associated with each);

Coordinate the programming of the panels and conferences (invitations to the panelists, drafting of content - descriptions, bio, photos - speakers' needs, etc.);

Organize networking activities;

Partnerships (15%)

In collaboration with the alliances department, establish and maintain strategic alliances and partnerships with various private and public partners;

Coordinate and ensure compliance with agreements with partners, funders and sponsors (activation, display, VIP management, special promotions, etc.);

Collaborate with the corporate alliances department to identify potential partners and to align the programming components with the sponsors' objectives;

Conduct a strategic watch on trends, initiatives and practices in the festival industry and more specifically in the music industry ;

Communications (15%)

In collaboration with the communications department, ensure an optimal presence with the various clienteles (professionals, general public, media and journalists, partners and collaborators);

Ensure that delivery deadlines are met for the various communications tools and promotional activities throughout the year or during events.

Occasionally represent the organization abroad at festivals and markets.

QUALIFICATIONS

University degree in cultural organization management, business administration or project management and/or significant experience in large-scale event production

Minimum of three (3) years experience in a similar position

Extensive knowledge of the event ecosystem and its partners

Ability and concrete experience in developing and monitoring a budget

Strong organizational and analytical skills

Ability to work under pressure and meet tight deadlines

Flexibility and availability in terms of working hours, approaching and during events

Strong team spirit

Perfect command of French and English, both spoken and written

Have a strong interest in the music industry, relevant experience in the entertainment or event industry, an asset

Mastery of MS Office software tools. Knowledge of Wordpress, Mailchimp, Airtable, Zone Festival and Lepointdevente ticketing software, an asset

